---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { loadStats } from '../lib/stats';
import { formatBytes, formatNumber } from '../lib/ssr';

const stats = loadStats();
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About — Essenfont"
  description="Essenfont is a universal Unicode 17 font — one redistributable OpenType file covering every assigned codepoint, assembled from 38 OFL-licensed donor fonts."
  canonical="/about"
>
  <article class="about">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>One font, every codepoint</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>Essenfont</strong> is a real font — not a library or a service. A single
        redistributable OpenType Collection (OTC) that covers every assigned Unicode 17
        codepoint ({formatNumber(stats.unicode.assignedCodepointCount)} characters across
        {stats.unicode.blockCount} blocks), built from {stats.donorCount} canonical
        OFL-licensed donor fonts.
      </p>
      <p>
        There is no UFO source, no hand-designed glyphs. Every glyph is vector-extracted
        from canonical donor fonts — Noto, Full-Sung, UniHieroglyphica, and more. The
        build is purely an assembly pipeline: read donors → partition by plane → stitch
        into subfonts → pack into a collection.
      </p>

      <h2>The name</h2>
      <p>
        <em>Essen</em> — German for "to eat" — because a universal font is meant to be
        consumed everywhere. The "font" is the object. Together: a font that eats every
        script.
      </p>

      <h2>The technical achievement</h2>
      <p>
        The canonical output is <code>Essenfont-Regular.otc</code> ({formatBytes(stats.fontBinaries.otcSizeBytes)}),
        a 10-face OpenType Collection with CFF2 outlines and CBDT color emoji bitmaps.
        The website serves {stats.websiteSubsets.woff2Count} per-block WOFF2 subsets ({formatBytes(stats.websiteSubsets.woff2TotalBytes)} total)
        so visitors don't download the full {formatNumber(stats.unicode.assignedCodepointCount)}-codepoint font just to
        browse one script.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every WOFF2 subset loads in Chrome's OpenType Sanitizer — a goal that required
        13 named fixes across three repos. See the <a href="/engineering">engineering story</a>
        for the full account.
      </p>

      <h2>License</h2>
      <p>
        Essenfont is distributed under the <strong>Open Font License (OFL) 1.1</strong>.
        Each donor's license terms are preserved in the font's <code>name</code> table and
        in the auto-generated <code>LICENSE-SOURCES.md</code>. See the
        <a href="/license">license page</a> for details.
      </p>

      <h2>Get it</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="/download">Download from GitHub Releases</a> or install via Fontist:
      </p>
      <pre><code>fontist install "Essenfont"</code></pre>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.about { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem 6rem; }
.page-head { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.eyebrow {
  font-family: var(--mono-font, 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace);
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.15em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--ef-rose, #bf4e6a);
}
h1 {
  font-family: var(--display-font, Spectral, serif);
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
  line-height: 1.1;
}
.prose h2 {
  font-family: var(--display-font, Spectral, serif);
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
}
.prose p { font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.7; }
.prose code {
  font-family: var(--mono-font, 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace);
  background: rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
  padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
  border-radius: 3px;
}
.prose pre {
  background: rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
  padding: 1rem;
  border-radius: 4px;
  overflow-x: auto;
}
.prose pre code { background: none; padding: 0; }
.prose a {
  color: var(--ef-rose, #bf4e6a);
  text-decoration: none;
}
</style>
